Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Since 19 Feb 2019, and as of 6 Mar 2019, 33 outbreaks of ASF have been officially confirmed in 6 provinces/cities: Thai Binh (n=19), Hung Yen (n=6), Hai Phong (n=5), Thanh Hoa (n=1), Ha Noi (n= 1), and Ha Nam (n=1).

According to OIE's WAHIS archived information, Viet Nam's ASF epidemiological statistics, as of 4 Mar 2019, were as follows:
Outbreak summary:
Total outbreaks: 33 (submitted)
Follow-up report no.: 5
Report reference: OIE Ref: 29741
Report date: 4 Mar 2019
Country: Viet Nam

Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Swine / 4238 / 1214 / 410 / 3828 / 0

The most recent follow-up report (no 5) was submitted by Viet Nam to the OIE on 4 Mar 2019, reporting a new outbreak in the village of Hien Thanh, Hai Duong province; see at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=29741

An interactive map, presenting all 33 outbreaks, as well as links to the relevant OIE reports since the start of the event, is available at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=29617.

No new outbreaks had been reported from China since 1 Mar 2019, when an immediate notification was submitted to the OIE, informing about a new outbreak in Haizetan village, Haizetan township, Jingbian, Yulin, Shaanxi; this event started on 17 Feb 2019 (see 20190302.6345075). However, on Thu 7 Mar 2019, China reported a new ASF outbreak in Guangxi; see at https://wsau.com/news/articles/2019/mar/07/china-reports-new-african-swine-fever-outbreak-in-guangxi-region/. - Mod.AS

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Viet Nam: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6354194,152]
